In a mixing bowl, combine the first six ingredients; beat on low speed until blended. Press into a greased 9-in. square baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in a saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate. Remove from the heat; stir in sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to the chocolate mixture and stir until smooth. Pour over crust. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until the top springs back when lightly touched. Cool on wire rack. In a mixing bowl, combine frosting ingredients; beat until smooth. Frost cooled brownies; cut.